OL,3,CLondon's future flood defences plans
OL,4,Cas 'sleeping giant' Thames Barrier
OL,5,Cturns 40
OL,7,FFlood defence walls through London
OL,8,Fwill need to be half a metre higher in
OL,9,Fthe future to protect against climate
OL,10,Fchange, officials said as they marked
OL,11,Fthe 40th anniversary of the Thames
OL,12,FBarrier.
OL,14,FThe barrier, officially opened by
OL,15,FQueen Elizabeth II, on May 8, 1984,
OL,16,Fand operated by the Environment
OL,17,FAgency, was designed to protect London
OL,18,Ffrom flooding until 2030, but the
OL,19,F"sleeping giant" is now expected to
OL,20,Ffunction until 2070.
