OL,3,CLondon's future flood defences plans
OL,4,Cas 'sleeping giant' Thames Barrier
OL,5,Cturns 40
OL,7,FIn the absence of the barrier, which
OL,8,Fis downstream from Greenwich and close
OL,9,Fto City Airport, the flood defence
OL,10,Fwalls that line the Thames through
OL,11,Fcentral London would have to have been
OL,12,Fbuilt up by another three metres,
OL,13,Fcutting off the city from its river.
OL,15,FBut with sea levels expected to rise
OL,16,Fby a metre by 2100 along with
OL,17,Fincreasingly intense storms driven by
OL,18,Fclimate change, officials say greater
OL,19,Fdefences against flooding will be
OL,20,Fneeded in the coming decades.
