OL,5,Cturns 40
OL,7,FThe other options are a new barrier
OL,8,Fwith a similar design to the current
OL,9,Fone, which has moveable gates that lie
OL,10,Fflat on the riverbed when not needed
OL,11,Fto allow vessels to pass through and
OL,12,Fthen swing up to close, or a permanent
OL,13,Fbarrier with locks for river traffic.
OL,15,FThe 40th anniversary also marks the
OL,16,Ffinal day in the job for Andy
OL,17,FBatchelor, who has been the Thames
OL,18,FBarrier's manager for 25 years, having
OL,19,Fstarted a new job at the site on the
OL,20,Fday it was opened by the late Queen.
